   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary78.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date when="1862-06-22">Sunday 22</date></dateline>
            <p>The day was exceedingly <name type="weather">hot</name> from about ten o’clock until
               2 when the <name type="weather">breeze</name> sprang up. </p>
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary79.jpg"/>
            <p><persName key="Col. George Schall"
                  ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper175"
                  >Lt. George Shall</persName> returned today. Yesterday and today we were in
               receipt of large <objectName type="readible">mails</objectName>, my <objectName
                  type="readible">letters</objectName> from <persName key="John Blair Linn"
                  ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper051"
                  >John</persName> running from the <date when="1862-06-06">6</date> to the 19th We
               have <objectName>papers</objectName> also of the 19th. <orgName type="company">Co A
               </orgName>had a special Inspection -<objectName> $5</objectName> to be given to one
               who had <objectName type="equipment">arms</objectName> and <objectName
                  type="equipment">accoutrements</objectName> in the best condition: This was the
               Springfield <objectName type="equipment">rifles</objectName>. They were most
               admirably gotten up. </p>
         </div>
